    {
      "step_idx": 5,
      "role": "Geospatial_Expert",
      "content": "It seems like we encountered a `403 Forbidden` error, which indicates that the service we are trying to use is not accessible due to insufficient privileges. This could be due to rate limiting or other restrictions.\n\nLet's switch to another geocoding service. We can use the `googlemaps` library for this purpose. To use the `googlemaps` library, we will need an API key. If you have a Google Maps API key, we can proceed. Otherwise, please obtain an API key from the Google Cloud Console.\n\nLet's use the `googlemaps` library to geocode the addresses. Here is the modified script:\n\n```python\nimport googlemaps\n\ndef geocode_address_gmaps(address, api_key):\n    gmaps = googlemaps.Client(key=api_key)\n    geocode_result = gmaps.geocode(address)\n    if geocode_result:\n        location = geocode_result[0]['geometry']['location']\n        return (location['lat'], location['lng'])\n    else:\n        return None\n\napi_key = \"YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY\"\n\nkarting_addresses = [\n    \"Ottostr. 7, 50859 Cologne\",\n    \"Am Aspel 6, 46485 Wesel\",\n    \"Max-Planck-Str. 11, 50769 Cologne\"\n]\n\nkarting_coordinates = []\n\nfor address in karting_addresses:\n    coordinates = geocode_address_gmaps(address, api_key)\n    karting_coordinates.append(coordinates)\n\nprint(\"Karting coordinates:\", karting_coordinates)\n```\n\nPlease replace `\"YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY\"` with your actual Google Maps API key. Once you provide the key, we can execute this script to get the coordinates of the karting tracks.\n\nCould you please provide the Google Maps API key so we can proceed?"
