    {
      "step_idx": 7,
      "role": "Geospatial_Expert",
      "content": "It seems the Google Maps API key provided is invalid. To proceed, we need a valid API key. Since we are unable to proceed with this method, let's switch back to using open data and APIs that do not require authentication. We can use OpenStreetMap's Nominatim service directly through the `requests` library.\n\nHere's an updated script using the `requests` library to geocode addresses using OpenStreetMap's Nominatim service:\n\n```python\nimport requests\n\ndef geocode_address_osm(address):\n    url = f\"https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/search?q={address}&format=json&limit=1\"\n    response = requests.get(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    if response.status_code == 200:\n        data = response.json()\n        if data:\n            return (data[0]['lat'], data[0]['lon'])\n        else:\n            return None\n    else:\n        return None\n\nkarting_addresses = [\n    \"Ottostr. 7, 50859 Cologne\",\n    \"Am Aspel 6, 46485 Wesel\",\n    \"Max-Planck-Str. 11, 50769 Cologne\"\n]\n\nkarting_coordinates = []\n\nfor address in karting_addresses:\n    coordinates = geocode_address_osm(address)\n    karting_coordinates.append(coordinates)\n\nprint(\"Karting coordinates:\", karting_coordinates)\n```\n\nLet's execute this script to get the coordinates of the karting tracks."
